==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cargo
<hw>Car"go</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Cargoes</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Sp. <ets>cargo</ets>,
<ets>carga</ets>, burden, load, from <ets>cargar</ets> to load, from
<ets>cargar</ets> to load, charge, See <er>Charge</er>.]</ety> <def>The
lading or freight of a ship or other vessel; the goods, merchandise, or
whatever is conveyed in a vessel or boat; load; freight.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Cargoes</qex> of food or clothing.</q> <rj><qau>E.
Everett.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The term <xex>cargo</xex>, in law, is usually applied to
goods only, and not to live animals or persons.</note>
<rj><au>Burill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cargoose</ent>⟦br⟧
